vulnerability.name: USN-7280-2
vulnerability.description: USN-7280-1 fixed a vulnerability in Python. This update provides the corresponding updates for some additional Python packages in Ubuntu releases. Original advisory details:   It was discovered that Python incorrectly handled parsing domain names  that included square brackets. A remote attacker could possibly use  this issue to perform a Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) attack.

statements.status_notes: Python could allow Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) attacks.
